Also, to get to the sol b rage afterr nagafen's death, you had to be there or go through the giants/greenies to get to it. The SF one is alot more accessible, thus easier to take, kill or camp, so either good or bad imo.<br>
Verant stated in the first patch message after their fix that the new RF spawns would be on a several day timer, with the one after patches being up to 3 days. Instead we got a 5-7 day spawn, with the spawn faster only after a patch. It seems to me that we went from about 2-3 epics a week to about 1-2 with the new changes. Only way for more is for multiple patches 2 days apart, and that very rarely happens. They slowed the pace of cleric epics entering the world even more imo. Stealth nerf? lol<br>
In my opinion, verant needs to take a long, hard look at the SF rage camp at least and find a workable solution before the situations connected to it get worse. They basically moved it so they wouldn't have as much CS problems, but just moved the problem to a new location and aggravated it. We get enough petitions to verant, and maybe they'll at least look into the problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uholyanlightwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Holyan Lightwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/18/02 2:24:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2233.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestion about Ragefire in Skyfire PLEASE READ AND POS</span><hr size=1> Ragefire = Serverious (sp?)<br>
